                <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uintus</ex></expan> Vera<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uinti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>fil</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Sera<supplied reason="lost">nus</supplied> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>vet</abbr><ex>eranus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> II <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>ic</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>e</abbr><ex>st</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex cert="low">eres</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>e</abbr><ex>x</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>t</abbr><ex>estamento</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Stele, rechte obere Ecke abgebrochen. Gefunden in sechs Fragmenten, zusammen mit einem Sockel aus Sandstein zur Einlassung der Stele. Z. 1: vielleicht Vera[nius, -tius, -cius vel sim.]; Z. 4: h(eres, -eredes).</p>
            </div>
